### Why
The original skill (v1.0.0) documented CI/CD migration for a Mojo/Python project (ProjectOdyssey). The 2026-04-26 session showed a distinct migration pattern for C++/CMake projects (ProjectKeystone) that uses a Makefile+justfile build system with `NATIVE=1` escape hatches rather than GitHub Actions composite actions. The Makefile variable replacement pattern (`DOCKER_CHECK`/`DOCKER_PREFIX` â†’ `CONTAINER_CHECK`/`CONTAINER_PREFIX`) and `Containerfile` adoption are reusable across any C++ project doing this migration.

